[nomarkup][Those are hideous pieces of art, but still - you recognize that this particular set looks like it is worth quite a bit. It had to be bought in one of the local galleries or on an auction. Such pieces often have stamps or notes on their back. It may even contain some useful information. Like when or where this set was bought. You stare at the picture which seems to be made under the acid influence for a minute and then dislodge it from the wall and look at it's back. You are not disappointed - indeed there is a paper stamp.][/nomarkup] #success
{$kieran}: Did you find something?
-> {$pcName}: I think so. Those are gallery or auction bought pieces.
    {$kieran}: Curious… Diana never hit me as an art enthusiast person. That is not as big enthusiast to buy paintings in the gallery.
    <<if GetIsPartyMemberRecruited($anastasia) is true>>
    {$anastasia}: Even if she is she has really bad taste.
    {$kieran}: You know how it is with tastes.
    <<endif>>
    <<jump paintingSuccessExamination>>
